      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T00:33:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The build status is already shown in the top-right, so we\u0027re not losing it.\n\nIn the linked bug, a user complains that having the status at the top of the main panel is distracting and just adds visual noise, while the build summary contains all relevant information (and now the background is coloured according to the status). So that\u0027s why I\u0027ve removed it.\n\nWhen there\u0027s no build summary, though, there\u0027s nothing here and it\u0027s slightly harder to tell at a glance if everything succeeded or not. So that\u0027s why I added the status back in only in case of there being no build summary (which often happens when a build succeeded).",
